<topic id="marklogic-contextual-actions">
  <title>MarkLogic Contextual Menu Actions</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Databases<indexterm>Connections<indexterm>MarkLogic<indexterm>Contextual menu
                actions</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>MarkLogic database contextual menu actions</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>While browsing MarkLogic connections in the <xref
        href="../topics/relational-database-explorer.dita#relational-database-explorer"
          ><uicontrol>Data Source Explorer</uicontrol> view</xref>, the various nodes include the
      following contextual menu actions:<dl>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><image href="../img/DbConnection16.gif"/> Connection Level Nodes</dt>
          <dd>
            <p>
              <dl>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/configure_data_sources">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/disconnect">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">
                  <dt><uicontrol>Link to Project</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Links the connection to a project. This is helpful for <xref
                      href="xquery-debugging-with-marklogic.dita#xquery-debugging-with-marklogic"
                      >MarkLogic debugging sessions</xref>.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/refresh">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/find_replace_in_files">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
              </dl>
            </p>
          </dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><image href="../img/DbCatalog16.gif"/> Container Level Nodes</dt>
          <dd>
            <p>
              <dl>
                <dlentry>
                  <dt><uicontrol>Enable Debug Mode</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Switches the server to a debugging mode.<ph
                      product="developer editor developerEclipse editorEclipse"> For more
                      information, see <xref
                        href="xquery-debugging-with-marklogic.dita#xquery-debugging-with-marklogic"
                        >MarkLogic debugging sessions</xref>.</ph></dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry id="use-it-to-execute-xquery">
                  <dt><uicontrol>Use it to Execute Queries</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>The server will be used to process XQuery expressions against it.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/refresh">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
              </dl>
            </p>
          </dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><image href="../img/DBModules16.png"/> Module or <image href="../img/NewFolder16.png"
            /> Folder Level Nodes</dt>
          <dd>
            <p>
              <dl>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/export">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/refresh">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
              </dl>
            </p>
          </dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><image href="../img/DBRequest16.png"/> Requests Level Nodes</dt>
          <dd>
            <p>
              <dl>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/refresh">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry id="cancel-all-requests">
                  <dt><uicontrol>Cancel all requests</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Cancels all queries that are either running or stopped on the application
                    server. You can use this action to clean up the entire
                      <uicontrol>Requests</uicontrol> container at the end of your sessions.</dd>
                </dlentry>
              </dl>
            </p>
          </dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><image href="../img/XslIcon16.gif"/> Resource Level Nodes</dt>
          <dd>
            <p>
              <dl>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/open">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/copy-location">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/refresh">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/compare">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
              </dl>
            </p>
          </dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl></p>
